{{Infobox book | name = Human Universe | image = Human Universe -- (book cover).jpg | caption = Hardcover edition | author = [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]], Andrew Cohen | language = English | genre = Non-fiction | subject = [[Humans]], [[popular science]] | publisher = [[William Collins (imprint)|William Collins]] | media_type = Print, e-book | pub_date = October 9, 2014 | pages = 288 pp. | isbn = 978-0007488803 | preceded_by = [[Wonders of Life (book)|Wonders of Life]] }}
'''''Human Universe''''' is a 2014 book by the [[Theoretical physics|theoretical physicists]] [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]] and Andrew Cohen. The book aims to explore [[Human]] [[life]] as well as understand what it is, and is explained in a way that is accessible to a general reader. The book is based on a series with the same name ''[[Human Universe]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Human Universe review – Brian Cox is taking a giant leap towards mankind|url = https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/oct/08/human-universe-review-brian-cox|website = the Guardian|accessdate = 2015-11-22|first = Sam|last = Wollaston}}</ref>
