{{biology-stub}}

'''Peter Wellnhofer''' (born [[Munich]], 1936) is a [[German people|German]] [[paleontologist]] at the "Bayerische Staatssammlung fur Paläontologie" in Munich. He is best known for his work on the various fossil specimens of ''[[Archaeopteryx]]'' or "Urvogel", the first known bird.  Wellnhofer's other work includes ''The Illustrated Encyclopedia of Pterosaurs''.

''[[Wellnhoferia]]'', a bird closely related to ''Archaeopteryx'', or a [[species]] of the Urvogel itself, was named in his honor.

In 2007 a special meeting of pterosaur experts in Munich was dedicated to Wellnhofer, describing him as "the foremost authority on pterosaurs for the last four decades."<ref>[http://flugsaurier.blogspot.com/2006/10/flugsaurier-wellnhofer-pterosaur.html flugsaurier.blogspot.com]</ref> The meeting produced a [[festschrift]] in his honor titled ''Flugsaurier: pterosaur papers in honour of Peter Wellnhofer''.<ref>[http://archosaurmusings.wordpress.com/2008/12/08/flugsaurier-pterosaur-papers-in-honour-of-peter-wellnhofer/ wordpress.com]</ref>

